<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened Runtime entitlements for Riven.

  Riven is an UNSANDBOXED terminal emulator. Deliberately no
  `com.apple.security.app-sandbox` key: sandboxing would trap the
  app in its container and block Full Disk Access entirely (even
  if the user granted it), and a terminal that can't read the
  user's files isn't a terminal.

  The exceptions below LOOSEN the Hardened Runtime for the Riven
  binary. They do NOT govern child processes — a shell or tool
  Riven spawns (in-process, via libghostty's PTY) gets its own
  code-signing context at exec. We ship the conventional terminal-
  emulator set (matches iTerm2) defensively: nothing in our own
  code strictly requires them today (we statically link libghostty
  and don't JIT), but they prevent edge-case breakage when the
  terminal is the "responsible process" for tools that do.

  Deliberately OMITTED:
    com.apple.security.cs.disable-executable-page-protection
      — disables W^X enforcement process-wide. The nuclear option;
        even iTerm2 doesn't ship it. Nothing we do needs it. Add it
        only if a specific tool demonstrably requires it.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Allow JIT-compiled code. Harmless for us; useful if an
         embedded interpreter ever runs in-process. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Allow pages that are both writable + executable. Required
         by JIT engines + some interpreters that might run under
         Riven's responsibility chain. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Don't strip DYLD_* environment variables. Dev workflows
         routinely set DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH / DYLD_INSERT_LIBRARIES;
         this keeps them intact through Riven's process boundary. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Allow loading libraries not signed by our Team ID. We
         statically link libghostty so this isn't needed for our
         own image, but it's standard for a terminal that may load
         or be attributed to third-party code. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
